original: The representation of gender in prehistoric and ancient works of art has been a subject of much analysis and interpretation. When examining iconic pieces such as the Venus of Willendorf and the Kouros statue, one can discern certain imbalances in gender equity, the assigned roles and responsibilities of men and women, as well as depictions of women as fertility agents and dependent creatures.
